Oman Sultan to Visit Russia for Nuclear Talks Mediation

### English Text Summary:
Oman's Sultan Haitham bin Tariq Al Said is set to visit Russia on Monday to meet with President Vladimir Putin as part of Oman's mediation efforts in crucial nuclear discussions between Washington and Tehran. This two-day visit follows an invitation from Putin and comes after a second round of talks between American and Iranian delegations regarding Iran's nuclear program in Rome. Oman has historically played a mediating role in these discussions, with the U.S. team led by Special Envoy Steve Biegun and the Iranian team led by Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi. Russia, which has a close alliance with Iran and participated in the 2015 nuclear agreement, is expected to play a significant role in any new agreement.

